text.section:
A sexual offender management team:
consists of:
a specially trained parole and probation agent; and
a representative of a sexual offender treatment program or provider; and
may include:
victim advocates or victim service providers with recognized expertise in sexual abuse and victimization;
faith counselors;
employment counselors;
community leaders;
a polygraph examiner with recognized expertise in sexual offender-specific polygraph examination;
a law enforcement officer;
an assistant State's Attorney;
an assistant public defender; and
a foreign or sign language interpreter.
